47:10.600 --> 47:12.200
Bessie? Take Valentine upstairs.

47:14.840 --> 47:16.998
There he is! Spineless worm!

47:17.000 --> 47:20.078
Let 'im come out an' answer to us!
If he dare!

47:26.160 --> 47:28.040
George Warleggan!

47:31.240 --> 47:33.438
What do they want?
Call the constables.

47:33.440 --> 47:35.560
Let him come out
and speak to his workers!

47:41.160 --> 47:42.720
Is he mad?

47:45.120 --> 47:46.278
Ross!

47:46.280 --> 47:47.718
Ross, wait.

47:47.720 --> 47:50.318
-Demelza.
-We must go to Trenwith.

47:50.320 --> 47:51.640
What is it?

47:53.360 --> 47:55.520
George Warleggan!

48:03.680 --> 48:06.838
Break th' door down! Go on!

48:06.840 --> 48:10.200
-Go on!
-Go on!
-Break it down!

48:13.720 --> 48:15.360
Tear th' 'ouse down!

48:23.080 --> 48:26.278
Sir George is not receiving
visitors.

48:26.280 --> 48:29.440
Well, Sir George has 'em,
whether he likes it or not.

48:39.600 --> 48:43.398
The very least these people
deserve is an apology.

48:43.400 --> 48:45.238
It's not my business to apologise.

48:45.240 --> 48:47.558
Leave my house
before I have you shot.

48:47.560 --> 48:51.678
No, sir, no, no, no,
that won't do at all.

48:51.680 --> 48:54.558
If you decline to come down and
speak civilly with these people,

48:54.560 --> 48:56.200
I'll come up there and fetch you.

49:02.040 --> 49:03.600
Let him deal with it.

49:13.280 --> 49:18.038
Sir George,
have you ever been unfairly treated?

49:18.040 --> 49:20.918
Can you comprehend what it is to
have no recourse or reparation,

49:20.920 --> 49:22.478
or even a fair hearing?

49:22.480 --> 49:24.440
Get out of my way.

49:26.280 --> 49:28.118
These people are not savages.

49:28.120 --> 49:30.920
All they ask is common decency.

49:32.240 --> 49:33.518
How do you answer?

49:33.520 --> 49:34.718
With this.

49:41.480 --> 49:42.878
Demelza, through here.

49:42.880 --> 49:44.118
My arm. My arm is broken!

49:44.120 --> 49:46.318
Ross, I told you this was
like to happen.

49:46.320 --> 49:48.198
For your own sake,
keep order out there, Ned.

49:48.200 --> 49:49.440
Demelza, help me.

49:54.480 --> 49:58.398
That man - he has stirred up the mob
- he has set them on a rampage.

49:58.400 --> 50:00.598
And what did you expect
when you closed a working mine?

50:00.600 --> 50:03.038
That folk'd celebrate,
that your name would be praised?

50:03.040 --> 50:05.358
-Do you seriously think I care?
-I think you do, George.

50:05.360 --> 50:09.000
As do I, which is why
I offer you a suggestion.

50:10.440 --> 50:12.958
Put those weapons down,
this is a peaceable protest.

50:12.960 --> 50:14.280
Come on!

50:15.680 --> 50:20.920
Friends. Friends, your anger
is wholly justified.

50:22.000 --> 50:24.360
But we have misunderstood
the situation.

50:25.400 --> 50:27.998
Sir George has explained it to me -

50:28.000 --> 50:31.200
and now begs leave
to explain it to you.

50:41.320 --> 50:44.318
Gentlemen, erm,

50:44.320 --> 50:47.478
I have been away in the north.

50:47.480 --> 50:53.600
And on my return discovered that my
orders were incorrectly carried out.

50:55.080 --> 50:58.080
The closure of Wheal Plenty
is temporary.

50:59.720 --> 51:02.918
This week, my mine captain
will assess the damage

51:02.920 --> 51:05.118
caused by the rock fall.

51:05.120 --> 51:07.878
All workers will be reinstated.

51:07.880 --> 51:12.958
And in addition, we will take on
more men in order to expedite

51:12.960 --> 51:15.200
a swift resumption of business.

51:17.200 --> 51:18.720
Do he expect us t' believe 'im?

51:20.240 --> 51:22.638
Should we not still hold
'im t' account?

51:27.160 --> 51:28.400
Right, let's get him!

51:30.520 --> 51:31.918
Whoa.

51:31.920 --> 51:33.440
This could take someone's eye out.

51:36.320 --> 51:37.878
Back off.

51:37.880 --> 51:40.478
Come on, people, back to your homes.

51:40.480 --> 51:42.200
You have what you came for.

52:02.120 --> 52:05.798
Your coming here was blatantly
provocative.

52:05.800 --> 52:08.118
I'm sorry you think so.

52:08.120 --> 52:12.998
You may thank the Lord I managed to
diffuse the situation so ably.

52:13.000 --> 52:14.998
Indeed, George.

52:15.000 --> 52:16.400
I salute you.

52:17.600 --> 52:19.160
Kindly leave my house.

52:22.200 --> 52:24.080
With pleasure.

52:35.760 --> 52:39.478
A fine thought - to let him
think 'twas his idea!

52:39.480 --> 52:42.158
It seemed the most elegant solution.

52:42.160 --> 52:44.358
And it saved us our estate.

52:44.360 --> 52:46.080
Ross.

52:47.160 --> 52:50.200
What you did -
what you were about to do...

52:51.280 --> 52:54.758
Understand, I love you
with all my heart.

52:54.760 --> 52:58.478
And I love your heart and your will
to make this world a better place.

52:58.480 --> 53:03.678
But...sometimes it'd seem
you overlook the cost.

53:03.680 --> 53:07.638
To we, as a family.
To we, as husband an' wife.

53:07.640 --> 53:10.758
Of course, I'd stand by you -
and even go without,

53:10.760 --> 53:12.638
for the sake o' the greater good.

53:12.640 --> 53:15.280
But...sometimes...

53:17.200 --> 53:19.878
..I feel that you
take that for granted.

53:19.880 --> 53:21.280
And I find that hard.

53:25.760 --> 53:27.958
You're too good for me.

53:27.960 --> 53:29.600
-No, Ross...
-I mean it.

53:31.480 --> 53:34.760
When I dragged you
from that dog-fight...

53:36.480 --> 53:39.238
..could I have known that you'd be

53:39.240 --> 53:41.360
the saving grace of my life?

53:51.760 --> 53:53.478
Here, race you back to Nampara?

53:53.480 --> 53:55.760
No contest!

54:07.800 --> 54:10.318
Did you come here to torment me?

54:10.320 --> 54:13.320
No. To complain.

54:14.920 --> 54:19.078
How monstrous,
inconvenient it is to discover

54:19.080 --> 54:22.280
so late in the day
that my heart is engaged.

54:24.000 --> 54:27.080
And not to the eminently
suitable Sir George.

54:28.920 --> 54:33.680
My father will never consent,
so I suppose we must elope.

54:36.120 --> 54:38.760
What? Who, you?

54:42.800 --> 54:45.000
And I?

54:50.920 --> 54:53.400
Could you bear it?

54:54.800 --> 54:56.998
Yes!

54:57.000 --> 54:58.680
Yes, I think I could bear it!

55:15.400 --> 55:18.558
Wheal Plenty open?
Who'd 'a b'lieved it?

55:18.560 --> 55:20.838
An' the real miracle is,
folk be that grateful

55:20.840 --> 55:23.118
they say they'll make donation to
the school.

55:23.120 --> 55:24.758
Maybe I need to
better my readin',

55:24.760 --> 55:27.118
since it seems th' school
shall 'ave need o' me.

55:27.120 --> 55:29.918
So...will 'ee teach me?

55:29.920 --> 55:31.320
Gladly.

55:39.000 --> 55:40.440
Everyone's happy.

56:02.280 --> 56:04.520
Oh, mistress, din' see 'ee there!

56:09.360 --> 56:11.720
I am your mistress no longer, Tess.

56:13.360 --> 56:15.958
Did you think you could remain
after what happened today?

56:15.960 --> 56:17.958
Ee be sendin' me away?

56:17.960 --> 56:22.358
What saddens me is that everyone
told me you mustn't be trusted.

56:22.360 --> 56:25.118
But I wanted to prove 'em wrong.

56:25.120 --> 56:26.760
Pack your things and go.

56:42.960 --> 56:45.160
Think 'ee've seen th' last o' me?

56:47.400 --> 56:48.600
Let's 'ope so!

56:59.080 --> 57:00.120
Come.

57:02.320 --> 57:04.800
A note from your informant, sir.

57:06.280 --> 57:12.478
A mob calling for revolution
led by Despard and Poldark

57:12.480 --> 57:17.360
stormed Trenwith and
assaulted Sir George Warleggen.

57:19.280 --> 57:23.880
Can such men be deemed loyal
to King and Country?

57:35.480 --> 57:37.318
He is the hero, I am the villain.

57:37.320 --> 57:38.718
So, what's the solution?

57:38.720 --> 57:39.998
Revenge.

57:40.000 --> 57:43.438
The bank has been obliged to issue
paper instead of coin.

57:43.440 --> 57:46.678
How hard can it be t' make
like notes?

57:46.680 --> 57:49.038
You stole him away?
What are you thinkin'?

57:49.040 --> 57:51.718
Lock him in the stables
and call the constables.

57:51.720 --> 57:54.678
Having such a document
in our possession would ensure

57:54.680 --> 57:56.158
immediate arrest.

57:56.160 --> 57:57.998
Death to the monarchy!

57:58.000 --> 57:59.198
We're going!

57:59.200 --> 58:02.040
If he falls, he takes you with him.

